WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:04.030 --> 00:00:08.050
It's all right! It's time to move on

3
00:00:08.310 --> 00:00:11.590
The sun shines always in our hearts

4
00:00:11.730 --> 00:00:15.010
Hand in hand, we convey our power

5
00:00:15.100 --> 00:00:18.680
And make our wishes come true

6
00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:32.490
Combining our strengths, we'll crest these surging seas

7
00:00:33.750 --> 00:00:40.290
Hurry toward the thrill of danger— Let the adventure begin!

8
00:00:40.960 --> 00:00:47.130
Now's the time to set sail; raise the anchor

9
00:00:47.930 --> 00:00:55.010
Off to the seas of adventure, through rainbow-colored winds

10
00:00:55.060 --> 00:00:58.550
Our journey's fraught with injury

11
00:00:58.560 --> 00:01:02.270
But what we cherish most is right at our side

12
00:01:02.400 --> 00:01:06.350
And if you get into a jam

13
00:01:06.450 --> 00:01:08.360
I'll always be there to protect you

14
00:01:09.450 --> 00:01:13.360
It's all right! It's time to move on

15
00:01:13.660 --> 00:01:16.820
The sun shines always in our hearts

16
00:01:17.170 --> 00:01:20.330
Shoulder to shoulder, we face all coming storms

17
00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:24.200
And look to the future for the light of hope

18
00:01:24.670 --> 00:01:27.920
If we gather up the pieces of our dreams

19
00:01:28.390 --> 00:01:31.550
They'll make a chart leading to tomorrow

20
00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:34.720
We come together under the same Jolly Roger

21
00:01:35.100 --> 00:01:40.450
And make our wishes come true; together, we are...

22
00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:56.220
<b>Impasse</b>

23
00:02:01.180 --> 00:02:04.450
Hey! Go get more food!

24
00:02:04.450 --> 00:02:06.300
We've got money now!

25
00:02:06.300 --> 00:02:08.140
The booze today is great!

26
00:02:12.610 --> 00:02:16.210
No one can top the years
I spent graffitiing on walls.

27
00:02:25.790 --> 00:02:28.460
Our money... they took it all.

28
00:02:28.460 --> 00:02:29.170
Nami...

29
00:02:30.500 --> 00:02:35.630
The crew... I can't face them.

30
00:02:37.120 --> 00:02:40.590
Give 'em hell, every last one of 'em!

31
00:02:47.110 --> 00:02:48.350
You sure 'bout that?

32
00:02:48.350 --> 00:02:50.400
Read 'em and weep!

33
00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:52.400
Now, go get the food!

34
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:56.190
Buy up everything at the store,
okay?! We've got the money!

35
00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:06.950
Well, damn! Don't go nowhere,
'cause I'll win next time!

36
00:03:12.880 --> 00:03:14.290
Huh?

37
00:03:27.220 --> 00:03:29.450
What?! What was that?!

38
00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:35.410
Who's there?!

39
00:03:35.410 --> 00:03:37.400
Who the hell are you?!

40
00:03:44.780 --> 00:03:46.720
That's...

41
00:03:55.540 --> 00:03:58.340
That's...

42
00:03:58.340 --> 00:04:00.780
Straw Hat Luffy!

43
00:04:12.710 --> 00:04:16.150
So you thought you'd come get
your money back, huh? How stupid!

44
00:04:16.150 --> 00:04:21.860
You see all of us? What could
the four of you possibly do?

45
00:04:24.110 --> 00:04:28.050
But, here you are. Word is,
you've got a bounty on your head.

46
00:04:28.050 --> 00:04:30.330
So why not leave your head with us?

47
00:04:31.700 --> 00:04:34.960
He's that long-nosed wimp's captain!

48
00:04:36.100 --> 00:04:39.900
So he can't be that tough!

49
00:04:43.670 --> 00:04:45.970
Bring it on, short stuff!

50
00:04:47.640 --> 00:04:50.550
Gum-Gum...

51
00:04:51.350 --> 00:04:52.850
Huh?

52
00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:56.770
What're you doing?

53
00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:03.500
He's using his bare fists? Even a battleship
wouldn't put a dent in that thick steel armor!

54
00:05:03.500 --> 00:05:04.700
What a joke!

55
00:05:06.700 --> 00:05:10.620
If you're just gonna fool around,
I'll go ahead and crush you.

56
00:05:27.800 --> 00:05:29.300
...Cannon!

57
00:05:36.440 --> 00:05:40.280
– What?!
– What?!

58
00:05:42.600 --> 00:05:46.000
H-He busted right through that thick armor!

59
00:05:46.950 --> 00:05:48.160
Hey!

60
00:05:49.100 --> 00:05:53.660
N-Now wait a minute, guys!
Let's talk things over!

61
00:05:53.660 --> 00:05:55.230
Let's talk...

62
00:05:55.230 --> 00:05:57.120
Let's... Let's...

63
00:05:57.120 --> 00:05:58.820
Let's fire the cannons!

64
00:05:58.820 --> 00:06:00.500
Yahoo!

65
00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:04.700
Three-Sword Style:

66
00:06:05.350 --> 00:06:06.470
Dire Raven...

67
00:06:12.800 --> 00:06:13.890
Hunt!

68
00:06:27.190 --> 00:06:30.570
Th-These cannonballs are
made of iron, you know!

69
00:06:38.010 --> 00:06:39.670
And the cannon?!

70
00:06:39.670 --> 00:06:43.270
Bad news! These guys are seriously bad news!

71
00:06:44.130 --> 00:06:48.130
L-Let's scram! Get out through the back door!

72
00:06:55.410 --> 00:07:00.350
You picked this fight.
Don't even think about backing out.

73
00:07:00.900 --> 00:07:02.480
Party Table...

74
00:07:03.230 --> 00:07:05.190
Kick Course!

75
00:07:17.790 --> 00:07:20.090
B-Back door's a no-go!

76
00:07:20.090 --> 00:07:22.500
The windows! Try the windows!

77
00:07:23.250 --> 00:07:24.380
Rumble!

78
00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:26.820
Horn Point!

79
00:07:36.970 --> 00:07:39.890
Roseo Colonnade!

80
00:07:45.870 --> 00:07:48.610
W-W-Wait a sec, you guys!

81
00:07:48.610 --> 00:07:51.710
It's the money, right?! That's what you want!

82
00:07:51.710 --> 00:07:55.030
The 200 million belly that loser had, right?

83
00:07:55.030 --> 00:07:59.000
Unfortunately, that money isn't here anymore!

84
00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:03.590
Our boss, Big Bro Franky,
took the money and went shopping.

85
00:08:03.590 --> 00:08:07.000
He's working a black-market deal,
so he could be anywhere by now!

86
00:08:07.910 --> 00:08:12.510
Basically, even if you go berserk here,
that 200 million belly won't come ba–

87
00:08:12.510 --> 00:08:14.140
I'm a goner!

88
00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:16.020
Ahh! Zambai!

89
00:08:18.010 --> 00:08:23.010
Stop running your mouth.
This was never about the money.

90
00:08:23.600 --> 00:08:26.810
Yeah. It's too late.

91
00:08:31.450 --> 00:08:34.010
After we're done, not even
your bones will remain.

92
00:08:34.740 --> 00:08:36.350
Not even our bones?!

93
00:08:36.350 --> 00:08:38.500
You idiot! Don't let 'im scare you!

94
00:08:38.500 --> 00:08:40.130
"Not even your bones will remain."

95
00:08:40.130 --> 00:08:44.670
That's our line! We're the Franky Family,
professional dismantlers and bounty hunters!

96
00:08:44.670 --> 00:08:48.210
Show 'em the Franky House specialty!

97
00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.640
Anything Goes Cannon!

98
00:09:05.700 --> 00:09:07.360
Here they come! Take 'em out!

99
00:09:07.990 --> 00:09:11.790
S-Stand tall! Keep firing until
we run out of projectiles!

100
00:09:11.790 --> 00:09:13.820
There're only four of 'em!

101
00:09:31.400 --> 00:09:32.510
Hm?

102
00:09:33.140 --> 00:09:35.450
What're those noises? Fireworks?

103
00:09:35.450 --> 00:09:38.510
They're coming from the northeast...
That's the Franky House!

104
00:09:38.510 --> 00:09:42.340
Them again? What's the big fuss this time?

105
00:09:42.340 --> 00:09:45.810
Yeah, it– Shh! He'll hear us!

106
00:09:48.690 --> 00:09:51.500
Oh, great. They're gonna tear the place apart.

107
00:09:51.500 --> 00:09:56.490
It sure as hell ain't no cocktail party.

108
00:09:56.490 --> 00:10:01.450
It's okay once in a while, right?
Today's a special day!

109
00:10:18.290 --> 00:10:20.300
Should we go after Franky?

110
00:10:20.300 --> 00:10:21.850
Where would he be?

111
00:10:23.010 --> 00:10:27.810
What a pain. Looks like they really
don't know where the money is.

112
00:10:28.330 --> 00:10:33.610
Even if we strangle this Franky guy,
he might've already spent the money.

113
00:10:33.610 --> 00:10:37.820
What now? We can wait around,
but he might not be back for a while.

114
00:10:38.370 --> 00:10:40.940
Hey! I finished giving him first aid!

115
00:10:40.940 --> 00:10:44.080
I need him on a stretcher. Give me a hand!

116
00:10:44.740 --> 00:10:46.960
We won't figure it out here.

117
00:10:46.960 --> 00:10:51.200
Let's go back to the ship for now.
Nami's all alone there.

118
00:10:51.200 --> 00:10:53.290
There's also Robin...

119
00:10:53.290 --> 00:10:55.890
and the issues with the ship too.

120
00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:56.710
Yeah.

121
00:10:57.210 --> 00:10:58.560
Hey, Luffy!

122
00:11:02.300 --> 00:11:04.010
About the ship...

123
00:11:04.010 --> 00:11:05.310
Hm?

124
00:11:05.310 --> 00:11:06.760
I've decided.

125
00:11:16.420 --> 00:11:20.970
This is where we say goodbye
to the Going Merry.

126
00:11:22.200 --> 00:11:26.120
<b>Galley-La Company
Headquarters</b>

127
00:11:26.520 --> 00:11:29.580
Well then, I'll be on my way.

128
00:11:31.700 --> 00:11:34.710
I can't believe how stubborn that guy is.

129
00:11:35.230 --> 00:11:41.060
We don't even know if he has it,
but they keep sending me out here anyway.

130
00:11:41.060 --> 00:11:43.550
I wish they'd put themselves in my shoes.

131
00:11:49.200 --> 00:11:50.400
It's Kalifa.

132
00:11:50.400 --> 00:11:52.520
Well... come in.

133
00:11:53.910 --> 00:11:56.500
You must be worn out, Mr. Iceburg.

134
00:11:56.500 --> 00:11:58.190
Something to drink?

135
00:11:58.190 --> 00:12:00.530
Yeah.

136
00:12:01.390 --> 00:12:03.390
Today, tea would be–

137
00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:04.870
Already brewed.

138
00:12:06.120 --> 00:12:08.800
Well, that's just like you, Kalifa.

139
00:12:08.800 --> 00:12:10.250
Thank you very much.

140
00:12:13.850 --> 00:12:16.990
Mr. Corgi tends to leave
in a bad mood, doesn't he?

141
00:12:16.990 --> 00:12:19.500
What in the world does he come to ask you?

142
00:12:19.500 --> 00:12:20.840
Oh, that.

143
00:12:20.840 --> 00:12:25.180
He wants something I have,
so he comes to persuade me to give it up.

144
00:12:27.400 --> 00:12:29.850
It must be something very precious, huh?

145
00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:35.060
Well, you see... I just tell him I don't know
what he's talking about and stonewall him.

146
00:12:35.550 --> 00:12:38.080
He's such a pain in the butt.

147
00:12:39.980 --> 00:12:41.140
Ah!

148
00:12:42.950 --> 00:12:45.820
Hey! Usopp woke up!

149
00:12:45.820 --> 00:12:48.920
Really?! That's great!

150
00:12:49.900 --> 00:12:51.700
Now we can relax a little.

151
00:12:55.360 --> 00:12:56.630
Hey, Usopp!

152
00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:05.590
Robin isn't back yet.

153
00:13:05.590 --> 00:13:09.560
Seriously, you shouldn't worry us like that!

154
00:13:10.800 --> 00:13:15.490
She's right. Marching in there
by yourself was reckless.

155
00:13:15.490 --> 00:13:18.400
You're lucky to be alive.

156
00:13:18.400 --> 00:13:20.890
Think before you act next time.

157
00:13:20.890 --> 00:13:23.350
Look who's talking!

158
00:13:25.900 --> 00:13:29.740
I'm sorry for being such a screw-up!

159
00:13:29.740 --> 00:13:30.960
I mean it...

160
00:13:30.960 --> 00:13:32.660
I'm such a failure!

161
00:13:32.660 --> 00:13:34.920
You guys!

162
00:13:37.870 --> 00:13:40.770
That money meant so much,
and I let it... I let it...

163
00:13:40.770 --> 00:13:44.380
Whoa, wait! Cool it!
I-I get it already, so let go!

164
00:13:44.380 --> 00:13:48.930
No really, we went through so much
to get that money and I...

165
00:13:48.930 --> 00:13:51.900
Usopp, you should still be in bed.

166
00:13:51.900 --> 00:13:56.020
Hey, you need to listen to Chopper.

167
00:13:57.300 --> 00:13:59.000
Then that's that.

168
00:13:59.660 --> 00:14:02.020
The money is gone for good, huh?

169
00:14:02.500 --> 00:14:07.070
Well, we won't know for sure
until this Franky guy comes back.

170
00:14:07.550 --> 00:14:10.240
I see. I'm sorry.

171
00:14:10.240 --> 00:14:14.200
But even if we don't get it back,
we still have 100 million belly.

172
00:14:14.200 --> 00:14:15.620
So it's okay. No worries.

173
00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:21.540
It's not okay! That's our money!

174
00:14:21.540 --> 00:14:22.510
Nami...

175
00:14:22.510 --> 00:14:24.800
Ah! My bad.

176
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:27.300
No, she's right.

177
00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:31.300
Anyway, Luffy, what about the ship?
What about the Merry?

178
00:14:31.300 --> 00:14:34.560
Will the remaining 100 million
be enough for her repairs?

179
00:14:35.150 --> 00:14:38.520
We're lucky we're at a first-class
shipyard that can fix her up.

180
00:14:38.520 --> 00:14:43.610
We'll have to refit her so she can
weather the seas ahead.

181
00:14:43.610 --> 00:14:45.530
Usopp, about that...

182
00:14:45.530 --> 00:14:47.800
We're getting a new ship.

183
00:14:47.800 --> 00:14:51.450
Sorry I didn't talk to you about it first,

184
00:14:51.450 --> 00:14:53.600
but I've already made up my mind.

185
00:14:53.600 --> 00:14:59.250
The Going Merry took good care of us,
but our journey with her ends here.

186
00:15:07.650 --> 00:15:08.760
Anyway...

187
00:15:09.280 --> 00:15:12.220
I took a look at the catalog Iceboss gave us.

188
00:15:12.220 --> 00:15:16.990
There're loads of different ships
to check out in here.

189
00:15:16.990 --> 00:15:20.690
If we go with a used one, 100 million
should get us a way bigger ship.

190
00:15:20.690 --> 00:15:21.920
Hold it...

191
00:15:22.650 --> 00:15:24.240
Just hold it, please.

192
00:15:24.240 --> 00:15:29.110
This joke... You're taking things
a little too far. Don't you think?

193
00:15:29.800 --> 00:15:33.890
I mean, look! Chopper's taking it seriously.

194
00:15:33.890 --> 00:15:37.590
Really though, someone tell our
captain to cut it out already.

195
00:15:37.590 --> 00:15:40.090
Say something to him, Nami.

196
00:15:43.700 --> 00:15:48.420
So then... we really don't...
have enough money to repair her?

197
00:15:48.420 --> 00:15:53.000
It's because I let them
steal the 200 million, isn't it?!

198
00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:55.230
Hey, that's what's going on, right, Luffy?

199
00:15:55.230 --> 00:15:58.500
A world-class shipyard would
charge premium prices, after all...

200
00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:00.180
No! That's not it!

201
00:16:00.180 --> 00:16:04.730
Then what is it?! Spit it out!
Are you sugarcoating this for my sake?!

202
00:16:04.730 --> 00:16:08.820
I'm not! This has nothing to do
with the money getting stolen!

203
00:16:08.820 --> 00:16:11.820
Then why the harebrained plan
to get a new ship?!

204
00:16:11.820 --> 00:16:13.240
Hey, stop it, you two!

205
00:16:13.240 --> 00:16:16.980
What good will bickering do?
Calm down, then talk!

206
00:16:18.410 --> 00:16:21.790
How can I calm down
after hearing this bullshit?!

207
00:16:21.790 --> 00:16:25.230
Hey! I get that this is important,
but you shouldn't get so worked up.

208
00:16:25.230 --> 00:16:29.200
She's right, Usopp. You'll get worse
if you don't take it easy.

209
00:16:29.200 --> 00:16:30.990
So then, I get worse!

210
00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:34.260
I can't relax when the captain
casually says we'll get a new ship!

211
00:16:34.610 --> 00:16:38.200
I wasn't being casual! I decided
after agonizing over it!

212
00:16:38.200 --> 00:16:40.890
And what exactly agonized you
about this decision?!

213
00:16:41.280 --> 00:16:44.440
You've got some nerve to spout off
while waving this around!

214
00:16:45.150 --> 00:16:46.360
Why'd you do that?!

215
00:16:46.850 --> 00:16:48.500
It was pissing me off.

216
00:16:48.500 --> 00:16:52.500
Tell me, Luffy, if it's not about
the stolen money, then what is it about?!

217
00:16:52.500 --> 00:16:56.490
Huh, Luffy?! Just say it already!
Hey! Why won't you tell me?!

218
00:16:56.490 --> 00:16:58.720
Don't hold back, no matter how much it stings!

219
00:16:58.720 --> 00:17:02.790
Say it! Why should I
go along with this?! Huh?!

220
00:17:02.790 --> 00:17:04.750
The Merry can't...

221
00:17:16.800 --> 00:17:20.220
What was... What did you just say?

222
00:17:20.860 --> 00:17:23.020
Don't make me repeat myself.

223
00:17:23.450 --> 00:17:26.800
The Merry... can't be repaired.

224
00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:29.360
There's just... no way to fix her.

225
00:17:31.780 --> 00:17:35.150
If there were, I wouldn't be talking like this.

226
00:17:35.150 --> 00:17:39.990
This ship?! You mean the ship
we're aboard right now?!

227
00:17:39.990 --> 00:17:43.500
That's right. This ship won't last much longer.

228
00:17:46.460 --> 00:17:48.800
What're you saying, Luffy?

229
00:17:48.800 --> 00:17:52.760
It's the truth. They told us at the shipyard.

230
00:17:53.890 --> 00:17:57.000
They said she won't even
reach the next island.

231
00:17:57.000 --> 00:18:00.280
Is that so? She won't, huh?

232
00:18:00.280 --> 00:18:04.410
You just met these guys today, and they've
already convinced you to walk away?

233
00:18:04.410 --> 00:18:06.000
Say what?

234
00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:09.900
I get that these top-notch shipwrights
gave you their assessment, but...

235
00:18:10.900 --> 00:18:13.890
you gave up just like that?!

236
00:18:13.890 --> 00:18:16.540
We've traveled together all this time!

237
00:18:16.540 --> 00:18:18.640
Past every wave! Through every battle!

238
00:18:18.640 --> 00:18:21.680
She's a precious member of this crew!

239
00:18:21.680 --> 00:18:25.510
And you're just gonna abandon
her in a place like this?!

240
00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:34.760
So that's it... Is that how little
this ship means to you, Luffy?!

241
00:18:36.590 --> 00:18:39.760
You shouldn't shout like that, Usopp.

242
00:18:39.760 --> 00:18:40.850
Please, step aside.

243
00:18:40.850 --> 00:18:41.760
What?

244
00:18:43.600 --> 00:18:46.020
I haven't gotten through to him yet.

245
00:18:46.020 --> 00:18:47.020
Usopp...

246
00:18:49.950 --> 00:18:52.730
Then can you make a more
accurate assessment?!

247
00:18:53.620 --> 00:18:58.500
We don't have our own shipwright.
That's why we got those guys to check her out!

248
00:18:58.500 --> 00:19:02.700
I get it, but asking guys like them
to fix her is pointless!

249
00:19:02.700 --> 00:19:05.880
I'll repair her like I always have!

250
00:19:05.880 --> 00:19:08.790
After all, that's how we made it this far.

251
00:19:08.790 --> 00:19:12.500
Alright! No time like the present!
Give me a hand, you guys!

252
00:19:12.500 --> 00:19:14.100
Hey, wait, Usopp.

253
00:19:14.100 --> 00:19:19.130
Oh, yeah, we don't have enough lumber.
I'll go buy some at the shipyard.

254
00:19:19.130 --> 00:19:21.180
Now, we've got a lot to do.

255
00:19:21.180 --> 00:19:23.600
You're not a shipwright, Usopp!

256
00:19:23.600 --> 00:19:24.720
Hold on, Luffy!

257
00:19:25.800 --> 00:19:28.100
Yeah, you're right. So what?!

258
00:19:28.100 --> 00:19:31.390
I don't trust shady shipwrights
who abuse their position

259
00:19:31.390 --> 00:19:37.250
and write things off because it's
"just another ship" to them!

260
00:19:37.250 --> 00:19:38.660
Usopp...

261
00:19:38.660 --> 00:19:43.290
The lesson here...? We need to
look out for the ship ourselves.

262
00:19:43.290 --> 00:19:48.190
I'll never give up on this ship!

263
00:19:48.840 --> 00:19:50.600
Did you lose your minds?!

264
00:19:50.600 --> 00:19:54.800
You all got taken in by those
smooth-talking shipwrights, didn't you?!

265
00:19:54.800 --> 00:19:58.920
The Luffy I know wouldn't have
fallen for some sales pitch.

266
00:19:58.920 --> 00:20:02.720
He would've been the first
to believe in the Merry's strength!

267
00:20:02.720 --> 00:20:06.810
But you didn't hesitate, acting like
some wise geezer with all the answers.

268
00:20:06.810 --> 00:20:09.790
What kind of captain makes
snap decisions like that?!

269
00:20:09.790 --> 00:20:12.020
I was wrong about you, Luffy!

270
00:20:12.360 --> 00:20:14.800
Wait a sec, Usopp! Luffy thought the same–

271
00:20:14.800 --> 00:20:17.900
Stay out of this, Nami!
This is something only I decided!

272
00:20:18.350 --> 00:20:19.400
And I won't budge.

273
00:20:19.400 --> 00:20:22.440
No matter what you say,
we're getting a new ship!

274
00:20:22.440 --> 00:20:24.320
We'll say goodbye to the Merry here!

275
00:20:24.320 --> 00:20:26.780
Like hell we will! I can't accept that!

276
00:20:26.780 --> 00:20:31.750
Listen, Luffy! Not everyone shares
your carefree attitude!

277
00:20:32.250 --> 00:20:35.920
I can't just leave our wounded friend here
and move on to the seas ahead!

278
00:20:35.920 --> 00:20:39.600
Don't give me that! Friend or not,
humans and ships are different!

279
00:20:39.600 --> 00:20:42.990
They're the goddamn same!
Merry still has some fight in her!

280
00:20:42.990 --> 00:20:47.170
But knowing you, you're probably just
excited about getting a new ship.

281
00:20:45.640 --> 00:20:49.430
You can't work this out if you're all fired up!

282
00:20:47.170 --> 00:20:49.430
Don't pretend to care about the Merry!

283
00:20:49.430 --> 00:20:50.930
Enough already!

284
00:20:50.930 --> 00:20:52.060
Luffy!

285
00:20:52.060 --> 00:20:54.290
You're not the only one hurting over this!

286
00:20:54.290 --> 00:20:55.940
Everyone here feels the same!

287
00:20:55.940 --> 00:20:58.480
If that were true, there's no way
you'd get a new ship!

288
00:20:58.480 --> 00:21:03.280
Fine! If you hate how I run things,
you should just lea–

289
00:21:07.130 --> 00:21:08.730
Sanji!

290
00:21:14.610 --> 00:21:19.210
You damn idiot.
What were you about to say?!

291
00:21:19.210 --> 00:21:23.970
Cool down before you end up saying
something you'll regret! Got that, Luffy?!

292
00:21:30.890 --> 00:21:33.990
Sorry. I just...

293
00:21:33.990 --> 00:21:38.060
That's okay, Luffy.
That's probably how you really feel.

294
00:21:38.500 --> 00:21:39.980
What'd you say?!

295
00:21:42.380 --> 00:21:47.820
Just get rid of the useless crewmates
that hold you back.

296
00:21:48.360 --> 00:21:50.280
If you're gonna abandon the Merry...

297
00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:53.290
why not do the same with me?!

298
00:21:53.290 --> 00:21:56.710
Hey, Usopp. Quit talking like that.

299
00:21:56.710 --> 00:21:58.900
No, I'm serious.

300
00:21:58.900 --> 00:22:01.170
It's been on my mind for a while.

301
00:22:02.740 --> 00:22:08.500
To be honest, I've been thinking that I can't
keep up with how monstrous you all are.

302
00:22:09.130 --> 00:22:12.470
Like today, I couldn't even guard the money.

303
00:22:14.470 --> 00:22:19.350
I'll just continue to be a burden on you guys.

304
00:22:23.390 --> 00:22:26.400
You don't need weak crew members, right?

305
00:22:26.400 --> 00:22:31.140
Luffy, you're the man
who'll be King of the Pirates.

306
00:22:31.890 --> 00:22:35.950
But I don't feel the need to go that far.

307
00:22:36.710 --> 00:22:43.670
Thinking back on it, I was about to sail off
on my own, when you invited me to join you.

308
00:22:44.140 --> 00:22:46.630
What're you talking about? Get on already.

309
00:22:47.020 --> 00:22:49.340
You're one of us now, aren't you?

310
00:22:53.190 --> 00:22:54.890
That's all that binds us.

311
00:22:57.300 --> 00:23:01.100
If we can't see eye to eye,
then why should we travel together?!

312
00:23:03.080 --> 00:23:06.110
Hey, where're you going, Usopp?!

313
00:23:06.780 --> 00:23:08.820
Where I'm going is my own business.

314
00:23:09.200 --> 00:23:12.530
It has nothing to do
with you guys anymore.

315
00:23:13.640 --> 00:23:14.580
I'm...

316
00:23:18.080 --> 00:23:21.120
leaving the crew.

317
00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:44.060
Why... Why aren't you saying anything?

318
00:23:47.150 --> 00:23:48.980
Usopp!

319
00:23:49.860 --> 00:23:52.780
Wait! This is all wrong!

320
00:23:52.780 --> 00:23:54.570
Hey! Turn around!

321
00:23:54.570 --> 00:23:56.200
Hey! Come back!

322
00:23:56.200 --> 00:23:59.410
Don't go, Usopp!

323
00:24:02.840 --> 00:24:06.090
Come back!

324
00:24:06.090 --> 00:24:07.380
Luffy...!

325
00:24:16.400 --> 00:24:20.390
Luffy! I can't follow you anymore.

326
00:24:21.600 --> 00:24:24.400
Sorry I dragged you down till the end.

327
00:24:26.690 --> 00:24:30.530
I realize that the ship
belongs to you, the captain.

328
00:24:32.500 --> 00:24:34.240
So fight me for her...

329
00:24:34.900 --> 00:24:36.870
Monkey D. Luffy!

330
00:24:44.600 --> 00:24:47.010
I challenge you to a duel!

331
00:24:53.880 --> 00:24:57.040
What? What? H-Hey... What're you saying?!

332
00:24:59.500 --> 00:25:04.770
At ten o'clock tonight, I'll come back here.

333
00:25:04.770 --> 00:25:07.900
Then we'll have a duel for the Merry!

334
00:25:07.900 --> 00:25:10.800
I'll defeat you and take her!

335
00:25:10.800 --> 00:25:11.690
And then...

336
00:25:12.380 --> 00:25:15.410
there'll be nothing left to bind us.
